cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL

This paper deals with performance prediction of OpenCL workloads on different compute devices, which is a topic related to performance modeling and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PF (Performance). Additionally, the paper discusses the characterization of OpenCL kernels and their features, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also deals with scheduling on HPC systems, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The methodology presented in the paper involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the methodology in OpenCL kernels, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
